The paper deals with the problem of lesion detection in medical images using deep learning techniques. Specifically, it proposes a novel extension to the popular Region Proposal Networks (RPNs) to detect lesion bounding ellipses. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms to optimize the detection process, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The experiments involve the use of a large medical image dataset, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of information retrieval techniques to compare the performance of different detection models, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
